                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/947a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-01-15">January 15,
                            1940</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department assumes that, in view of the absence of reports from you on the
                    subject, the British prize court and contraband control base reported to have
                    been established in Palestine by the British Government have not attempted to
                    function.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
